Package: superassp
Type: Package
Title: Speech Signal Processing Using Various Frameworks with a wrassp-like Interface
Version: 2.7.1
Date: 2026-05-22
Authors@R: c(
    person("Fredrik", "Nylén", , "fredrik.nylen@umu.se", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3373-0934"))
  )
Maintainer: Fredrik Nylén <fredrik.nylen@umu.se>
Description: Bundles routines for speech and voice signal processing, either
  continuously throughout the recording (trk_* functions) or producing acoustic
  summaries of a portion of the signal (lst_* functions). Example acoustic
  properties that can be tracked throughout a signal include f_o/pitch (for
  which several algorithms have been implemented), formant frequencies and
  bandwidths, harmonics-to-noise ratio, harmonics and harmonic differences,
  cepstral peak prominence, and numerous others. Several can be tracked at once
  using comprehensive assessment toolkits like Praat Sauce or Voice Sauce.
  Summary assessments (lst_* functions) include toolkits for voice analysis,
  voice tremor analysis, and comprehensive summaries via bundled openSMILE
  configurations. Results are returned either as a 'wrassp'-compliant
  AsspDataObj (which may be stored to disk in an SSFF-formatted file) or as a
  JSON format (JSTF) that more efficiently stores dense spectral information
  for a limited, specific portion of the signal.
